Will the videos be added to the gallery on /firefox/video/?
That would simplify linking since we only need to point to that page with a query string for the video title, e.g. "http://www.mozilla.com/firefox/video/?video=fx4-features", and the page loads the specified video. That also covers all the multi-format cross-platform issues when they send the link to someone who may not be using Firefox. So in that case I don't need the direct video URL, just the name to use in the query string.

Here's the updated copy for the installation guides. Made some edits and cuts. Let me know what you think.
INSTALLING FIREFOX ON WINDOWS
STEP 1 Visit mozilla.com with any browser (i.e. Internet Explorer) and click the download button.
STEP 2 Click Run to start the installation process.
For Windows Vista/Windows 7: Once Firefox finishes downloading, a User Account Control window will appear. Click Yes to proceed.
STEP 3 Almost there! Click Next on the welcome screen to continue.
STEP 4 This will bring you to the Setup Type screen. A standard setup is selected by default, which will install Firefox with a recommended configuration that will work for most users.
STEP 5 Click Finish to close the setup wizard when installation is complete. If the “Launch Firefox now” box is checked, Firefox will start immediately.
CONGRATULATIONS! You are now ready to enter a bold new era of Web surfing. Double-click on the Firefox icon whenever you want to go online.
For more step-by-step instructions and useful tips and tricks visit: firefox.com/tour
INSTALLING FIREFOX ON MAC
STEP 1 Visit mozilla.com with any browser (i.e. Safari) and click the download button.
STEP 2 Your file will begin downloading automatically in a few seconds.
STEP 3 Once Firefox has finished downloading, the disk image may open by itself. If not, double-click the Firefox dmg icon to open it.
STEP 4 A Finder window will appear. Drag the Firefox icon into the Applications folder.
STEP 5 Drag the Firefox icon from the Applications folder into the dock.
CONGRATULATIONS! You are now ready to enter a bold new era of Web surfing. Simply click on the Firefox icon whenever you want to go online.
For more step-by-step instructions and useful tips and tricks visit: firefox.com/tour
